# KPI Layout Patterns

## Problem: Grid vs. List Layout
Avoid 2x2 or 4-column grids for KPI data under publisher info. Use consistent list layout instead.

## Correct Pattern: List Layout
Use `flex justify-between` for consistent alignment like other metadata:

```typescript
{/* CORRECT: List layout like publisher info */}
<div className="mt-3 pt-2 border-t space-y-1 text-xs">
  <div className="flex justify-between gap-8">
    <span className="text-muted-foreground">Ort. D0 ROAS:</span>
    <span className="font-semibold text-blue-600">
      {formatROAS(avgD0Roas)}
    </span>
  </div>
  <div className="flex justify-between gap-8">
    <span className="text-muted-foreground">Ort. D7 ROAS:</span>
    <span className="font-semibold text-green-600">
      {formatROAS(avgD7Roas)}
    </span>
  </div>
  <div className="flex justify-between gap-8">
    <span className="text-muted-foreground">Ort. Günlük Install:</span>
    <span className="font-semibold text-purple-600">
      {averageDailyInstalls.toFixed(0)}
    </span>
  </div>
</div>
```

## Incorrect Pattern: Grid Layout
Avoid this pattern for metadata sections:

```typescript
{/* INCORRECT: Don't use grid for metadata */}
<div className="grid grid-cols-2 gap-2 text-xs">
  <div>
    <span>Ort. D0 ROAS:</span>
    <div className="font-semibold">{formatROAS(avgD0Roas)}</div>
  </div>
  {/* ... */}
</div>
```

## When to Use Grid vs. List

### Use Grid Layout For:
- Main dashboard KPI cards
- Equal-importance metric cards
- Independent data cards

```typescript
{/* Main dashboard metrics */}
<div className="grid gap-4 md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-4">
  <MetricsCard title="Total Installs" value={totalInstalls} />
  <MetricsCard title="Average ROAS" value={avgRoas} />
</div>
```

### Use List Layout For:
- Metadata under main content
- Secondary information
- Publisher details and related KPIs
- Any data that should align consistently

```typescript
{/* Publisher metadata */}
<div className="space-y-1">
  <div className="flex justify-between gap-8">
    <span>Ülke:</span>
    <span className="font-medium">{country}</span>
  </div>
  <div className="flex justify-between gap-8">
    <span>Platform:</span>
    <span className="font-medium">{platform}</span>
  </div>
  <div className="flex justify-between gap-8">
    <span>Publisher:</span>
    <span className="font-medium">{publisher}</span>
  </div>
</div>
```

## Consistent Styling
- Use `text-muted-foreground` for labels
- Use `font-medium` or `font-semibold` for values
- Use `gap-8` for consistent spacing
- Add color coding for value types (blue for D0, green for D7, etc.)

